==English==
===Etymology===
Supposedly originated in the 19th century [[Royal Navy]] as a waking call<ref>National Maritime Museum [http://www.nmm.ac.uk/server/show/conWebDoc.17897]</ref>.

===Verb===
'''to [[show]] a [[leg]]'''

# {{cattag|idiomatic|nautical}} To [[wake up]] and get out of [[bed]]. (''Used mostly in the [[imperative]]'').
#:'''''Show a leg''' or you're going to be late.''

